01:14:54.120 --> 01:14:57.400
the least violent in history.

01:14:59.680 --> 01:15:03.280
So, we haven't got very far down the course to nonviolence,

01:15:03.280 --> 01:15:05.760
but I don't see why we shouldn't just carry on doing it.

01:15:05.760 --> 01:15:07.760
I think it's ridiculous, frankly.

01:15:08.880 --> 01:15:13.200
Excuse my frankness, to say that violence is a good thing.

01:15:14.320 --> 01:15:16.840
I think that it would be a wonderful concept

01:15:16.840 --> 01:15:19.720
if we could evolve somehow to a world

01:15:19.720 --> 01:15:22.080
3,000 years from now,

01:15:22.080 --> 01:15:26.800
where violence is really regarded as simply appalling

01:15:26.800 --> 01:15:29.920
and that they look back on our time

01:15:29.920 --> 01:15:32.560
and can't believe what we were doing.

01:15:32.560 --> 01:15:35.760
Yeah, but of course violence takes a lot of different shapes

01:15:35.760 --> 01:15:37.360
as we start to think deeper and deeper

01:15:37.360 --> 01:15:40.280
about living beings on Earth.

01:15:40.280 --> 01:15:41.920
For example, the violence we commit

01:15:41.920 --> 01:15:43.960
and the torture we commit to animals.

01:15:43.960 --> 01:15:45.240
And then perhaps down the line,

01:15:45.240 --> 01:15:48.560
as we talked offline about, is with robots

01:15:48.560 --> 01:15:49.360
and that kind of thing.

01:15:49.360 --> 01:15:52.640
So, there's just so many ways to commit violence to others.

01:15:52.640 --> 01:15:56.040
And some people now talk about violence in the space of ideas,

01:15:56.040 --> 01:15:58.000
which of course, to me at least,

01:15:58.000 --> 01:16:00.280
is a bit of a silly notion relative

01:16:00.280 --> 01:16:04.040
to use that same V word for the space of ideas

01:16:04.040 --> 01:16:06.440
versus actual physical violence.

01:16:06.480 --> 01:16:09.000
But it may be that long time from now,

01:16:09.000 --> 01:16:12.000
we see that even violence in the space of ideas

01:16:12.000 --> 01:16:16.760
is quite a manifestation of that same kind of violence.

01:16:16.760 --> 01:16:19.520
And so, it is interesting where this is headed.

01:16:20.400 --> 01:16:23.080
And I think you're absolutely right.

01:16:23.080 --> 01:16:27.640
A world, a nonviolent world does seem like a better world.

01:16:27.640 --> 01:16:30.680
I wonder if the constraints on resources

01:16:30.680 --> 01:16:34.440
somehow make that world more and more difficult,

01:16:34.440 --> 01:16:36.200
especially as we run out of resources.

01:16:36.240 --> 01:16:37.480
It's got to be very, very different

01:16:37.480 --> 01:16:39.120
from what we're doing nowadays.

01:16:39.120 --> 01:16:40.920
And it's unimaginably different.

01:16:40.920 --> 01:16:41.840
If we could imagine it,

01:16:41.840 --> 01:16:43.680
then maybe we could work towards it at the moment.

01:16:43.680 --> 01:16:45.520
Nobody knows how to work towards it.

01:16:45.520 --> 01:16:47.000
Well, that's kind of the stories of humans

01:16:47.000 --> 01:16:48.680
as we don't really know the future.

01:16:48.680 --> 01:16:53.240
We're trying to ad hoc kind of develop it as we go

01:16:53.240 --> 01:16:57.080
and sometimes get into trouble as to violence.

01:16:57.080 --> 01:17:02.080
But George Orwell's vision in 1984 was of two or three

01:17:03.080 --> 01:17:04.680
world powers, each so powerful

01:17:04.680 --> 01:17:09.680
that nobody could diminish the, could destroy the other.

01:17:11.720 --> 01:17:16.000
But the notion of an evolutionarily stable relationship

01:17:16.000 --> 01:17:21.000
among heavily armed world powers just does not seem,

01:17:23.760 --> 01:17:27.280
as though it's reasonable at all.

01:17:27.400 --> 01:17:32.400
There's to say, we've now got 170 or 190 nations in the world,

01:17:36.240 --> 01:17:40.560
dominated by a few big ones, all with arms

01:17:40.560 --> 01:17:42.240
pointing at each other.

01:17:42.240 --> 01:17:45.360
And the notion that we could just carry on

01:17:45.360 --> 01:17:49.280
having peace talks and making sure that these arms

01:17:49.280 --> 01:17:54.120
don't get involved in some kind of massive conflagration

01:17:54.120 --> 01:17:57.000
seems incredibly optimistic.

01:17:57.040 --> 01:18:00.240
Some kind of major change has to happen,

01:18:00.240 --> 01:18:03.200
whereby, and some people wouldn't like to see

01:18:03.200 --> 01:18:05.160
all the weapons go, that'd be great.

01:18:05.160 --> 01:18:07.920
I'm a member of that sort of group

01:18:07.920 --> 01:18:10.680
that tries to see that happen.

01:18:10.680 --> 01:18:13.160
It's gonna be very difficult to see it happen.

01:18:13.160 --> 01:18:16.120
Another kind of concept is the nations themselves

01:18:16.120 --> 01:18:21.120
will dissolve and will become one government.

01:18:21.880 --> 01:18:23.760
That itself is a terrifying vision

01:18:23.800 --> 01:18:28.120
because the capacity for abuse by a single world power

01:18:28.120 --> 01:18:30.800
would be so problematic.

01:18:30.800 --> 01:18:32.520
And in addition, how do you get there

01:18:32.520 --> 01:18:34.200
without a war in the first place?

01:18:35.280 --> 01:18:39.120
So at the moment, we have no reasonable kind

01:18:39.120 --> 01:18:42.080
of future in mind, but I'm sure it's there somewhere.

01:18:42.080 --> 01:18:43.640
It's just that we haven't yet to find it.

01:18:43.640 --> 01:18:46.080
And a lot of people like in the cryptocurrency space

01:18:46.080 --> 01:18:49.680
argue that you can create decentralized societies

01:18:49.680 --> 01:18:52.360
if you take away the power from states

01:18:52.360 --> 01:18:54.120
to define the monetary system.

01:18:54.120 --> 01:18:58.720
So they argue like, if you make the monetary system

01:18:58.720 --> 01:19:01.280
such that it's disjoint from the control

01:19:01.280 --> 01:19:03.960
of any one individual, any one government,

01:19:03.960 --> 01:19:06.680
then that might be a way to form sort of ad hoc,

01:19:06.680 --> 01:19:08.000
decentralized societies.

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:10.840
They just pop up all over the place.

01:19:10.840 --> 01:19:13.920
That's a really interesting technological solution

01:19:13.920 --> 01:19:17.240
to how to remove the overreach of power

01:19:17.240 --> 01:19:18.080
from governments.

01:19:18.080 --> 01:19:20.040
Yes, right, absolutely.

01:19:20.040 --> 01:19:24.520
And it may well be that the future will emerge

01:19:24.520 --> 01:19:28.680
out of some sort of quite surprising direction like that.

01:19:28.680 --> 01:19:31.200
Is it nevertheless surprising to you

01:19:31.200 --> 01:19:34.320
that we have not destroyed ourselves with nuclear weapons?

01:19:34.320 --> 01:19:36.520
So the mutually assured destruction

01:19:36.520 --> 01:19:38.480
that we've had for many decades

01:19:38.480 --> 01:19:40.800
from somebody who studies violence,

01:19:41.880 --> 01:19:43.280
how does that make sense to you?

01:19:43.280 --> 01:19:45.480
Well, I mean, I'm surprised only in the sense

01:19:45.480 --> 01:19:50.000
that accidental, the fact that we have not had

01:19:50.000 --> 01:19:54.520
an accident yet has been quite remarkable.

01:19:54.520 --> 01:19:56.080
Because all the accounts are

01:19:56.080 --> 01:19:59.320
that we've come very close to having very serious accidents

01:19:59.320 --> 01:20:03.160
where people are either side of misread intentions

01:20:03.160 --> 01:20:05.320
or apparent launches and so on.

01:20:06.960 --> 01:20:08.680
So yes, I think it is remarkable.

01:20:08.680 --> 01:20:13.680
There is a nasty generalization that can be made

01:20:14.160 --> 01:20:19.160
that the longer that powerful states go

01:20:19.160 --> 01:20:23.500
without having wars, then the worse the war is afterwards.

01:20:25.400 --> 01:20:28.520
And you can sort of see that that kind of makes sense

01:20:28.520 --> 01:20:32.120
because basically what's happening with these tribal groups

01:20:32.120 --> 01:20:37.120
that the nations are at the moment is that after a big war

01:20:37.320 --> 01:20:39.120
like the Second World War,

01:20:39.120 --> 01:20:42.200
they established new kinds of dominance relationships.

01:20:42.200 --> 01:20:45.800
And then during the periods of peace,

01:20:45.800 --> 01:20:50.800
what happens is that the de facto dominance relationships

01:20:51.720 --> 01:20:54.560
change because some nations become poorer,

01:20:54.560 --> 01:20:56.000
some become richer,

01:20:56.000 --> 01:20:58.600
some become more militarily powerful and so on.

01:20:58.600 --> 01:21:02.320
Generally economy and military goes hand in hand.

01:21:02.320 --> 01:21:05.560
So right now China emerged from the war

01:21:05.560 --> 01:21:09.560
as a relatively low status state and is now high status.

01:21:09.560 --> 01:21:11.040
So if this was chimpanzees,

01:21:11.040 --> 01:21:13.160
what would happen is that you would predict a conflict

01:21:13.200 --> 01:21:16.200
because you need to have a readjustment

01:21:16.200 --> 01:21:18.320
of the formal dominance relationships

01:21:18.320 --> 01:21:22.360
to recognize the new in-practice dominance relationships

01:21:22.360 --> 01:21:24.800
recognized by the economy and the military.

01:21:26.080 --> 01:21:29.280
So the longer that you have of a period of peace

01:21:29.280 --> 01:21:30.520
following a war,

01:21:30.520 --> 01:21:33.880
then the more these tensions of unresolved,

01:21:33.880 --> 01:21:37.200
changed dominance relationships build up.

01:21:37.200 --> 01:21:39.600
And the longer they take to occur,

01:21:39.600 --> 01:21:44.600
then the more challenging are gonna be the conflicts.

01:21:46.320 --> 01:21:47.480
That's a terrifying view

01:21:47.480 --> 01:21:50.520
because we've been out of conflict for quite a bit.

01:21:50.520 --> 01:21:51.360
That's right.

01:21:51.360 --> 01:21:52.680
Maybe it's building up.

01:21:52.680 --> 01:21:53.560
So it's a scary view.

01:21:53.560 --> 01:21:55.080
But on the other hand,

01:21:55.080 --> 01:21:59.800
things have changed hugely with the advent of nuclear weapons

01:21:59.800 --> 01:22:04.800
because at least that conforms to this psychology

01:22:05.120 --> 01:22:06.800
that is very clear in other animals,

01:22:06.800 --> 01:22:08.880
which is you don't want to get into a fight

01:22:08.920 --> 01:22:11.160
if you are going to get hurt.

01:22:11.160 --> 01:22:15.760
So that's the whole principle of MAD, Mutual Assured Destruction.

01:22:15.760 --> 01:22:18.680
And it's doubtless being why powerful nations

01:22:18.680 --> 01:22:21.960
like America and Russia

01:22:21.960 --> 01:22:25.600
have not used their nuclear weapons since 1945.

01:22:27.480 --> 01:22:32.240
So if we can overcome the problem of accidental launches,

01:22:33.200 --> 01:22:37.360
then maybe the fact of MAD does fit into human psychology

01:22:37.400 --> 01:22:41.480
in a way that means that we really will resolve our tensions

01:22:41.480 --> 01:22:42.600
without using them.

01:22:42.600 --> 01:22:47.520
But we haven't yet really faced that challenge.

01:22:47.520 --> 01:22:49.760
I mean, the Soviet Union collapsed

01:22:49.760 --> 01:22:52.240
because of the poor economy,

01:22:52.240 --> 01:22:57.240
but with China desperate to take back Taiwan

01:22:58.560 --> 01:23:03.560
and America shifting its focus on the Pacific,

01:23:04.200 --> 01:23:05.920
the potential for something going wrong

01:23:06.040 --> 01:23:07.200
is clearly very high.

01:23:08.080 --> 01:23:11.440
So what's the hopeful case that you can make

01:23:11.440 --> 01:23:15.840
for a long-term surviving and thriving human civilization

01:23:15.840 --> 01:23:18.120
given all the dangers that we face?

01:23:19.760 --> 01:23:22.200
Well, I can't really exactly make one.

01:23:22.200 --> 01:23:27.200
I would just say that we're talking about the dangers.

01:23:27.520 --> 01:23:29.920
Obviously the dangers are there.

01:23:29.920 --> 01:23:34.560
But what I would sort of think about is the notion

01:23:34.560 --> 01:23:39.560
that surprises come from all sorts of different directions.

01:23:40.640 --> 01:23:44.920
And I mean, you work in robotics

01:23:44.920 --> 01:23:49.760
and I can well imagine that there will be advances

01:23:49.760 --> 01:23:52.920
in robotics that in some way I can't even conceive

01:23:52.920 --> 01:23:57.920
will somehow undermine the motivation for conflict.

01:23:58.080 --> 01:24:01.760
Something about, by the time chips have been planted

01:24:01.760 --> 01:24:05.600
in human brains and we're all instantly sharing information

01:24:05.600 --> 01:24:07.600
in a way that we never did before,

01:24:08.480 --> 01:24:12.040
will this change the nature of human existence

01:24:12.040 --> 01:24:15.120
in such a way that these conflicts get resolved?

01:24:15.120 --> 01:24:17.760
So remove the conflicts but keep some of the magic,

01:24:17.760 --> 01:24:19.640
the beauty of what it means to be human.

01:24:19.640 --> 01:24:21.560
So like still be able to enjoy life,

01:24:21.560 --> 01:24:24.720
the richness of life, the full complexity of life.

01:24:24.720 --> 01:24:28.360
Cause you can remove conflict by giving everybody a pill

01:24:28.360 --> 01:24:30.480
and then they go to sleep, right?

01:24:30.480 --> 01:24:35.480
You still want life to be amazing, exciting, interesting.

01:24:37.200 --> 01:24:39.960
And so that's where you have to find the balance.

01:24:39.960 --> 01:24:43.000
Well, it's, yes, I mean, it's all science fiction stuff

01:24:43.000 --> 01:24:47.760
and so how it's gonna work out totally unclear.

01:24:50.760 --> 01:24:55.080
I don't see any worry about the magic of life disappearing.

01:24:55.080 --> 01:24:57.920
I mean, first of all, you somehow get rid of males.

01:24:57.920 --> 01:25:00.080
I think you really need to get rid of males

01:25:00.080 --> 01:25:05.080
cause males are the source of a major problem,

01:25:05.680 --> 01:25:10.680
which is the lust for power and the resulting conflict.

01:25:11.000 --> 01:25:14.400
But you don't think the males are also source of beauty

01:25:14.400 --> 01:25:15.240
and creation?

01:25:15.240 --> 01:25:18.160
No, no, I mean, I don't have anything against males

01:25:18.160 --> 01:25:20.880
as individuals and that sort of thing.

01:25:20.880 --> 01:25:22.840
And males have clearly done a lot.

01:25:22.840 --> 01:25:27.080
I mean, they've been incredibly exploratory and creative

01:25:27.080 --> 01:25:30.960
and what they've done in art and music has been wonderful

01:25:30.960 --> 01:25:32.160
and that sort of thing.

01:25:32.160 --> 01:25:35.320
On the other hand, I'm not sure there's anything

01:25:35.320 --> 01:25:37.880
particularly special and I think that probably females

01:25:37.880 --> 01:25:39.840
could do the same thing just as well

01:25:39.840 --> 01:25:40.960
when given the chance.

01:25:42.240 --> 01:25:44.320
Yes, including the dark stuff.

01:25:44.320 --> 01:25:48.000
I mean, a part of me is not understanding the,

01:25:48.000 --> 01:25:52.640
so there is evolutionary distinction between men and women,

01:25:52.640 --> 01:25:55.760
but I tend to believe both men and women,

01:25:55.800 --> 01:25:58.680
if you look out into the future, it can be destructive,

01:25:58.680 --> 01:26:00.120
it can be evil, it can be greedy,

01:26:00.120 --> 01:26:02.040
it can be corrupted by power.

01:26:02.040 --> 01:26:03.680
So if you move males from the picture,

01:26:03.680 --> 01:26:06.520
which are historically connected to this evolution

01:26:06.520 --> 01:26:08.720
of that we've been talking about,

01:26:08.720 --> 01:26:11.960
that women are gonna fill that role quite nicely

01:26:11.960 --> 01:26:15.120
and then it'll be just the same kind of process,

01:26:15.120 --> 01:26:20.120
not the same, but it'll be new and interesting.

01:26:20.600 --> 01:26:25.440
There's a sense that the will to power, craving power,

01:26:25.440 --> 01:26:28.280
committing violence is somehow coupled

01:26:28.280 --> 01:26:32.640
with all the things that are beautiful about life,

01:26:32.640 --> 01:26:35.160
that if you remove conflict completely,

01:26:35.160 --> 01:26:37.800
if you remove all the evil in the world,

01:26:38.800 --> 01:26:43.800
it seems like you're not going to have a stable place

01:26:47.600 --> 01:26:49.520
for the beauty for the goodness.

01:26:49.520 --> 01:26:54.520
Like there's always has to be a dragon to fight for the way,

01:26:55.000 --> 01:26:56.200
if you look at human history,

01:26:56.200 --> 01:26:58.880
now you can say the reason I'm nervous

01:26:58.880 --> 01:27:02.400
about a sort of utopia where everything is great

01:27:02.400 --> 01:27:04.680
is every time you look through human history

01:27:04.680 --> 01:27:06.760
when the utopia has been chased,

01:27:06.760 --> 01:27:09.880
you run into a lot of trouble where again,

01:27:09.880 --> 01:27:13.720
sneaks into this evil, this craving for power.

01:27:13.720 --> 01:27:16.680
Now you can say that's a male problem,

01:27:16.680 --> 01:27:18.960
but I just think it's a human problem

01:27:18.960 --> 01:27:22.160
and it's not even a human problem, it's a chimp problem too.

01:27:22.200 --> 01:27:24.600
It's life on earth problem, intelligent life

01:27:24.600 --> 01:27:25.600
on earth problem.

01:27:25.600 --> 01:27:30.600
So like it's better to not necessarily get rid

01:27:30.800 --> 01:27:34.640
of the sources of the darkest sides of human nature,

01:27:34.640 --> 01:27:38.160
but more create mechanisms that the kindness,

01:27:38.160 --> 01:27:41.840
the goodness as the goodness paradox, your book,

01:27:41.840 --> 01:27:46.840
that that is incentivized and encouraged, empowered.

01:27:47.760 --> 01:27:52.760
Well, look, I don't think it would be utopia

01:27:54.280 --> 01:27:56.480
if you got rid of the males.

01:27:56.480 --> 01:27:57.320
Right.

01:27:58.240 --> 01:28:00.560
And certainly females capable of conflict.

01:28:01.600 --> 01:28:03.280
I just think it's a gamble worth taking

01:28:03.280 --> 01:28:04.880
if you could actually do it.

01:28:04.880 --> 01:28:07.120
You can certainly find females in history

01:28:07.120 --> 01:28:11.280
who've done unpleasant things, but nevertheless,

01:28:11.280 --> 01:28:13.480
we have a very strong evolutionary theory

01:28:13.520 --> 01:28:17.000
which explains why males benefit more

01:28:17.000 --> 01:28:21.560
by having conflict and winning conflicts than females do.

01:28:22.520 --> 01:28:27.520
And so if we want to talk about reducing conflict,

01:28:28.200 --> 01:28:29.040
yes.

01:28:29.040 --> 01:28:31.960
Then it would reduce it to get rid of males.

01:28:31.960 --> 01:28:34.120
Now I understand this is a fantasy.

01:28:34.120 --> 01:28:37.160
And I think it's a fantasy that people would be able

01:28:37.160 --> 01:28:40.560
to talk about fairly soon because reproductive technology

01:28:40.560 --> 01:28:44.320
is getting to the point where it's quite likely

01:28:44.320 --> 01:28:49.320
that human females could breed without the use of males.

01:28:50.560 --> 01:28:55.560
And so there would be a sort of potential dynamic

01:28:55.680 --> 01:29:00.680
if everybody just agreed not to have any male babies.

01:29:01.800 --> 01:29:03.760
It's a really interesting thought experiment.

01:29:03.760 --> 01:29:07.440
I will agree with you that if given two buttons,

01:29:07.440 --> 01:29:09.640
one is get rid of all women

01:29:09.640 --> 01:29:11.800
and the other buttons get rid of all men.

01:29:14.000 --> 01:29:18.680
Realizing that I have a stake in this choice,

01:29:18.680 --> 01:29:20.800
you're probably getting rid of all men.

01:29:20.800 --> 01:29:25.680
If I wanted to preserve earth

01:29:25.680 --> 01:29:28.440
and the richness of life on earth,

01:29:28.440 --> 01:29:30.280
I would probably get rid of all men.

01:29:30.280 --> 01:29:31.120
I don't know.

01:29:31.120 --> 01:29:32.680
I don't think you have a stake in it.

01:29:32.680 --> 01:29:35.960
I mean, you're saying that because you're a man.

01:29:35.960 --> 01:29:38.560
But I don't see why being a man

01:29:38.560 --> 01:29:40.400
should make you any more interested

01:29:40.400 --> 01:29:43.880
in having a male future for the world than a female future.

01:29:43.880 --> 01:29:46.640
You've got just as many ancestors who were male

01:29:46.640 --> 01:29:48.440
as were female.

01:29:48.440 --> 01:29:50.520
Well, my problem is I'll have to die.

01:29:51.520 --> 01:29:53.800
Well, that's gonna happen anyway.

01:29:53.800 --> 01:29:57.120
I know, but I prefer to die tomorrow and not today.

01:29:58.400 --> 01:30:00.560
I prefer to hit the snooze button

01:30:00.560 --> 01:30:02.840
on the whole mortality thing.

01:30:02.840 --> 01:30:03.800
But it's interesting.

01:30:03.800 --> 01:30:05.640
But this is not suggesting that males have to die

01:30:05.640 --> 01:30:06.880
in order to make room for females.

01:30:07.880 --> 01:30:11.480
All you have to do is just say,

01:30:11.480 --> 01:30:13.920
don't let's have any more males born.

01:30:13.920 --> 01:30:14.760
Interesting.

01:30:14.760 --> 01:30:18.240
Of course, the difficulty is that because we're tribal,

01:30:18.240 --> 01:30:20.080
