02:31:46.080 --> 02:31:52.080
If you're too deadly, that's a big problem. If you're not deadly enough, that's also a problem.

02:31:52.080 --> 02:31:55.080
So that is a fascinating exploration of...

02:31:55.080 --> 02:32:01.080
I don't see any evidence. There's no way you're coming from when you say that being too peaceful is a problem.

02:32:01.080 --> 02:32:12.080
Well, because, I'll say it this way, death is a way to get rid of suboptimal solutions.

02:32:13.080 --> 02:32:16.080
But there's lots of ways to die without violence.

02:32:16.080 --> 02:32:19.080
Right. To me, death in itself is violence.

02:32:19.080 --> 02:32:31.080
And a lot of people that talk about, for example, longevity and disease and all that kind of stuff, they see death is the way they talk about it.

02:32:31.080 --> 02:32:37.080
And it's interesting to think of it that way. Death is like mass murder that's happening.

02:32:38.080 --> 02:32:47.080
People that try to, from a biological perspective, help extend life, they see that you're helping...

02:32:47.080 --> 02:32:58.080
The biggest atrocity in the history of human civilization, from their perspective, is not allocating all our resources to solving death.

02:32:58.080 --> 02:33:06.080
Right. Because death is a kind of violence. It is a kind of murder that we're allowing to be committed on us by nature.

02:33:07.080 --> 02:33:14.080
So the flip side of that is death makes way for new life, for new ideas.

02:33:14.080 --> 02:33:24.080
Yes, but that's got nothing to do with peace versus war. You have animals that are very, very peaceful, but they evolve just in the same way as other animals do.

02:33:24.080 --> 02:33:28.080
They just don't do it with death caused by violence.

02:33:28.080 --> 02:33:34.080
And violent death is premature death, surely. I mean, I don't mind about people dying.

02:33:34.080 --> 02:33:40.080
What I mind about is people dying in their youth.

02:33:40.080 --> 02:33:46.080
Prematurely, but some people would say all death is premature. It certainly feels that way.

02:33:46.080 --> 02:33:52.080
It's died too soon. Anyone who's ever died died too soon.

02:33:52.080 --> 02:34:00.080
Yeah. Well, I mean, if we can become like sequoias and live for hundreds of years or thousands of years, that would be great.

02:34:00.080 --> 02:34:04.080
Do you ponder your own mortality? Are you afraid of death?

02:34:04.080 --> 02:34:10.080
I don't think I'm afraid of it. You know, I'm reconciled to the fact it's going to happen.

02:34:10.080 --> 02:34:19.080
I just feel frustrated because I enjoy life, you know, and I don't want to, to leave the party.

02:34:19.080 --> 02:34:25.080
Yeah, it's kind of a fun party. I don't want to leave the party either.

